<body>
An integration test suite project that can be used for functional integration testing of SOAP webservice endpoints. It is built on top of <a href="http://testng.org/">TestNG testing framework</a>, spring webservices (<a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-ws/site/">spring-ws</a>) project and uses <a href="http://code.google.com/p/jetlang/">Jetlang</a> and <a href="http://groovy.codehaus.org/">Groovy</a>.

<h2>Installation</h2>
Pre-requisites: Please have maven 3+ and <a href="http://www.springsource.com/developer/sts">Spring source tool suite</a>(or eclipse) installed. This project relies on the groovy-eclipse compiler in order to compile the code and not maven java or groovy compiler. If that is unviable please modify the pom accordingly. You also need to install the Groovy feature(including the optional 1.8 compiler) in STS/eclipse. If you are using plain vanilla eclipse, then M2Eclipse and EGit plugins need to be installed
apart from the groovy eclipse plugin.

<ul>
<li>git clone git@github.com:menacher/Test-Tools.git</li>
<li>cd Test-Tools</li>
<li>mvn eclipse:eclipse - Takes time!</li>
<li>eclipse -> file -> import -> git -> select repository and import</li>
<li>ws-int-test project in eclipse -> right click on pom.xml -> run as -> maven test - takes time!</li>
</ul>

If everything works as expected you should see some test cases executed successfully!

Happy coding!
